@namespace DotNetCloud.Modules.Example.UI

@*
    Help content for the Example module.
    Serves as a reference template for other module help components.
*@

<div class="help-content">
    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Overview</h2>
        <p>The Example module is a reference and demo module for module developers. It demonstrates how to build a complete module with UI components, data storage, and event handling following DotNetCloud's module system conventions.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Creating Notes</h2>
        <p>To create a new note:</p>
        <ol class="help-steps">
            <li>Click the <strong>+ New Note</strong> button on the notes page.</li>
            <li>Fill in the title and content fields in the note form.</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Save</strong> to create the note.</li>
        </ol>
        <p>The new note will appear at the top of the notes grid.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Editing Notes</h2>
        <p>Click on an existing note's content area to edit it inline. Changes are saved automatically.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Deleting Notes</h2>
        <p>Each note card has a delete button. Click it to remove the note. There is no undo — deletion is immediate.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Tips &amp; Tricks</h2>
        <ul class="help-tips">
            <li>Use the Example module as a reference when building your own modules.</li>
            <li>The module demonstrates patterns for forms, lists, events, and data persistence.</li>
            <li>Check the source code at <code>src/Modules/Example/</code> for implementation details.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">FAQ</h2>
        <dl class="help-faq">
            <dt>Can I use this module in production?</dt>
            <dd>No. The Example module is for development reference only and is not intended for production use.</dd>
            <dt>How do I create my own module?</dt>
            <dd>Use the Example module as a template. Copy the structure and replace the namespaces, then implement your specific functionality.</dd>
        </dl>
    </section>
</div>
